spans.text: Thoughts of thee , Boldly attempts the Dangers of the Sea
East to West , over Rocks and Quicksands
he prises Riches more than Breath
By thee misled , Not Conscience , Quicksands , Rocks , or Death
who find their wearied Taste Palled with the Prospect of the cumbrous Feast
their wearied Taste Palled with the Prospect of the cumbrous Feast
It's nobler cheerfully to bear our Fate , Than murmur and repine beneath its Weight
the Praise of human Kind , Who bears ill Fortune with a Christian Mind : How does his great heroic Soul aspire Above that sordid Wealth the rest admire
of human Kind , Who bears ill Fortune with a Christian Mind : How does his great heroic Soul aspire Above that sordid Wealth the rest admire
Hold forth the heavenly Prise , which makes him run His mortal Race
of the Proud , Not all the Censures of the grovelling Crowd , Not Poverty
the solid Quiet of his Breast
the Darts , which adverse Fortune throws
a steady Rock , sublimely steep , Within the Confines of the briny Deep
